e werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Elizabeth, your role in this game is wolf.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Amanda': 'Susan', 'Elizabeth': 'Kelly', 'Rhonda': 'Kelly'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Amanda', 'Elizabeth', 'Rhonda']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 4\n - Final Target: Kelly\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nPlayers deceased during the night: Kelly, Devin\nLast words from Kelly: Fellow villagers, I am sorry to be eliminated so early, but I must share my suspicions with you. I believe Devin and Amanda are the werewolves. Devin's elimination with me on the first night is suspicious, as werewolves often target each other to mislead the group. Amanda's behavior has been inconsistent, and she seemed overly eager to protect Devin, which is unusual for a villager. Be cautious and gather more evidence before making accusations. Trust Elizabeth and Susan, and verify information before acting. Good luck to you all.\nPlayer Devin has been eliminated from the game.\nPlayer Kelly has been eliminated from the game.\nAmanda's speech: Thank you for letting me speak. I want to address Kelly's last words. While I understand her suspicions, I believe we need to be cautious and gather more evidence before making accusations. I deny being a werewolf and can explain my actions last night. I protected Devin because I believed he was in danger, and I wanted to ensure his safety. I also want to support Elizabeth and Susan, as Kelly suggested. Their behavior has not been suspicious, and I trust their judgment. Let's work together to gather more information and make informed decisions.\nAntionette's speech: Thank you, Amanda, for your thoughtful speech. I agree that we need to be cautious and gather more evidence before making accusations. Last night was peaceful, which is a positive sign, but we should remain vigilant. I noticed that Elizabeth and Susan's behavior has not been suspicious, and I trust their judgment. Amanda's actions last night could be seen as suspicious, but it's also possible that she genuinely believed Devin was in danger. Let's work together to gather more information and make informed decisions. We should not jump to conclusions and should continue to observe the players' behavior carefully.\nElena's speech: Thank you, Amanda and Antionette, for your thoughtful speeches. I agree that we need to be cautious and gather more evidence before making accusations. The peaceful night is a positive sign, but we should remain vigilant. I have noticed that Elizabeth and Susan's behavior has not been suspicious, and I trust their judgment. Let's continue to observe the players' behavior carefully and verify information before acting. We should not jump to conclusions and should work together to make informed decisions.\nElizabeth's speech: Thank you for letting me speak. I believe it's crucial that we remain cautious and gather more evidence before making accusations. I want to address Kelly's last words and support Amanda and Susan, as she suggested. I trust their judgment and believe they have not been suspicious. I also want to share a piece of information from my check last night. I saw that one of the players was not a werewolf, but I cannot reveal who it was. Let's work together to gather more information and make informed decisions. We should not jump to conclusions and should continue to observe the players' behavior carefully.\nElizabeth's speech: Thank you